@Database CFG_FileID

@Index HBBS:Docs/Misc/Index.guide/MAIN

@Node Main "FileID's, Last Upated on 30-06-1996"

  Description
  ===========

  The HBBS:System/FileID file defines the options and commands that
  are used to extract/add file descriptions to files.

  Adding
  ======

    A file (described by the {A} code below) must have a the description
    stored in the a file (described by the {D} code) added to the file,
    overwriting any description already in the file.

  Getting
  =======

    The file (described by the {A} code below) must have a the description
    extracted and stored in another file (described by the {D} code)


  Options: (All options MUST be set at the moment..)                                 *C*
  ==================================================

    FileExtension_XX=<String>       @{" More... " link FileExtension}
    FileType_XX=<String>            @{" More... " link FileType}
    MaxDIZLines_XX=<Numeric>        @{" More... " link MaxDizLines}

    AddDiz_XX=<CommandString>       @{" More... " link AddDIZ}
    Add_CDToWork_XX=<Boolean>       @{" More... " link Add_CDToWork}
    Add_CDToPlayPen_XX=<Boolean>    @{" More... " link Add_CDToPlaypen}
    Add_RenameDIZ_XX=<Boolean>      @{" More... " link Add_RenameDIZ}

    GetDIZ_XX=<CommandString>       @{" More... " link GetDIZ}
    Get_CDToWork_XX=<Boolean>       @{" More... " link Get_CDToWork}
    Get_CDToPlayPen_XX=<Boolean>    @{" More... " link Get_CDToPlaypen}
    Get_RenameDIZ_XX=<Boolean>      @{" More... " link Get_RenameDIZ}


  Codes
  =====

    The following Codes are used in the GetDIZ_XX and AddDIZ_XX parameters.

    All examples are based on a file called Test.LHA being uploaded to Node1


    {A} is replaced with the full path and filename of the uploaded file
        e.g. HBBS:Nodes/Node1/PlayPen/Test.LHA

    {F} is replaced with the filename of the uploaded file
        e.g. Test.LHA

    {N} is replaced with the filename (but not the extension) of the file
        e.g. Test

    {E} is replaced with the extension of the file
        e.g. LHA

    {W} is replaced with the full path of the WORK directory
        e.g. HBBS:Nodes/Node1/Work

    {P} is replaced with the playpen direcotry
        e.g. HBBS:Nodes/Node1/PlayPen

    {D} is replaced with the full path and filename of the DIZ file
        to be added/extracted
        e.g. HBBS:Nodes/Node1/Work/Test.LHA.DIZ

  Full Example of all parameters to cope with .LHA archives
  =========================================================

    FileExtension_1=LHA
    FileType_1=LHA Archive
    MaxDIZLines_1=12
    AddDIZ_1=LHA <>nil: u -m {A} FILE_ID.DIZ
    Add_CDToWork_1=TRUE
    Add_CDToPlayPen_1=FALSE
    Add_RenameDIZ_1=TRUE
    GetDIZ_1=LHA <>nil: e -m {A} FILE_ID.DIZ
    Get_CDToWork_1=TRUE
    Get_CDToPlayPen_1=FALSE
    Get_RenameDIZ_1=TRUE

@EndNode

@Node FileExtension "FileExtension"

  FileExtension_XX=<String>

    E.G.

    FileType_1="LHA"

    No Default, Must Be Set!

    Everything after the . in a filename is a file extension.  HBBS compares
    the extension of the file uploaded to this setting, if they are the same
    then it knows what kind of file it is and the other options tell hbbs how
    to handle it.

@EndNode

@Node FileType "FileType"

  FileType_XX=<String>

    E.G.

    FileType_1="LHA Archive"

    No Default, Must Be Set!

    This string describes the type of file uploaded, maximum 15 chars.
    This may be displayed to the user by the bbs software during file checking.

@EndNode

@Node AddDIZ "AddDIZ"

  AddDIZ_XX=<CommandString>

    E.G.

    AddDIZ_1="LHA <>nil: u @F@ @D@"

    No Default, Must Be Set!

    This options specified the command used to add a modified/new file
    description to a file.

@EndNode

@Node Add_CDToWork"Add_CDToWork"

  Add_CDToWork_XX=<Boolean>

    E.G.

    Add_CDToWork_XX=TRUE

    Default = FALSE

    This option when enabled makes the bbs software change to the current node's
    WORK directory (normally HBBS:Nodes/NodeX/Work/ ) before it runs the
    @{"AddDIZ_XX" link AddDiz} command

@EndNode

@Node Add_CDToPlayPen "Add_CDToPlaypen"

  Add_CDToPlaypen_XX=<boolean>

    E.G.

    Add_CDToPlaypen_XX=TRUE

    Default = FALSE

    This option is the same as @{"Add_CDToWork" link Add_CDToWork} except it changes to the PLAYPEN
    directory for the current node (where the uploaded file would be stored).

@EndNode

@Node Add_RenameDIZ "Add_RenameDIZ"

  Add_RenameDIZ_XX=<boolean>

    E.G.

    Add_RenameDIZ_XX=TRUE

    Default = FALSE

    if you don't use the {D} code in your AddDiz_XX command line then your
    diz adder program probably wants the file to be called FILE_ID.DIZ before
    it is stored.  If you specify this parameter, the Work/<Filename>.DIZ is
    renamed to Work/FILE_ID.DIZ before AddDIZ_XX is called

    Example, LHA needs the file containing the file description to be called
    FILE_ID.DIZ before it adds it to the archive, whereas DMSDescript does not

    Checkout the example config file for a better idea of how it works..

@EndNode

@Node MaxDIZLines MaxDIZLines""

  MaxDIZLines_XX=<numeric>

    E.G.

    MaxDIZLines_XX=10

    Default = Defaults to the setting in NodeGlobal or NodeLocal

    This is the same as the option specified in  the file:
    @{"HBBS:Conferences/<confname>/ConfConfig" link ConfConfig.guide/MaxDIZLines}

@EndNode



@Node GetDIZ "GetDIZ"

  GetDIZ_XX=<CommandString>

    E.G.

    GetDIZ_1="LHA <>nil: u -m {A} FILE_ID.DIZ"

    No Default, Must Be Specified!

    This command is used to extract the file_id from the uploaded file.

@EndNode

@Node Get_CDToWork"Get_CDToWork"

  Get_CDToWork_XX=<Boolean>

    E.G.

    Get_CDToWork_XX=TRUE

    Default = FALSE

    This option when enabled makes the bbs software change to the current node's
    WORK directory (normally HBBS:Nodes/NodeX/Work/ ) before it runs the
    @{"GetDIZ_XX" link GetDiz} command

@EndNode

@Node Get_CDToPlayPen "Get_CDToPlaypen"

  Get_CDToPlaypen_XX=<boolean>

    E.G.

    Get_CDToPlaypen_XX=TRUE

    Default = FALSE

    This option is the same as @{"Get_CDToWork" link Get_CDToWork} except it changes to the PLAYPEN
    directory for the current node (where the uploaded file would be stored).

@EndNode

@Node Get_RenameDIZ "Get_RenameDIZ"

  Get_RenameDIZ_XX=<boolean>

    E.G.

    Get_RenameDIZ_XX=TRUE

    Default = FALSE

    if you don't use the {D} code in your GetDiz_XX command line then your
    diz extractor program probably wants the file to be called FILE_ID.DIZ before
    it is stored.  If you specify this parameter, the Work/<Filename>.DIZ is
    renamed to Work/FILE_ID.DIZ before GetDIZ_XX is called

    Checkout the example config file for a better idea of how it works..

@EndNode


